content.name: Persona1-Msg1
content.textContent:
Cancer-related fatigue is frequently said to be one of the most common and stressful symptoms of living with cancer. So, I wanted to pass along this link to information on cancer-related fatiguethat you may find helpful.
To help you get started, I am including a link to a web page that contains information about the advanced treatment options available at our new CTCA® Outpatient Care Center, located in downtown Chicago. This new location is easy to travel to by public transportation or by car. You also have access to convenient parking.

content.name: Persona2-Msg1
content.textContent: As you continue to address your cancer care, I want to share valuable information I think you will find useful.  Please click on this link to learn about important options for managing pain

ajisedq56cm.superContent: Choosing the right hospital is one of the most important decisions you make in your cancer journey, and I want to commend you for exploring your treatment options. You deserve to find targeted treatment options available for your specific type of cancer, delivered by a team of experts. Understanding your options plays a key role in that decision

content.name: Persona1-Breast-Msg1
content.textContent: One important factor to keep in mind as you proceed with your cancer treatment is the overall treatment results of the cancer center where you are receiving treatment. Clear and thorough information on survival, quality-of-life and patient satisfaction results can help you determine which provider may be best suited to treat your type of cancer.

content.name: Cancer Type-Leukemia - Acute Lymphatic-Msg1
content.textContent: My friend, I understand this is a complex topic. To help, I am linking to more information about the promise of precision cancer treatment, genomic testing and the benefits precision cancer treatment can offer. Whether precision cancer treatment is right for you is a decision you make with your medical team based on your individual situation. However, at CTCA, we believe that the more information you have, the better informed decisions you can make about your own cancer treatment.

content.name: Cancer Type-Leukemia, Blood-Msg1
content.textContent: Cancer Treatment Centers of America® (CTCA) sponsors this site to ensure that all patients, regardless of where they receive cancer treatment, have access to valuable information related to their cancer diagnosis, symptoms and treatment. If you would like to receive ongoing updates, you can also sign up to receive a weekly cancer newsletter

content.name: Breast-Msg1
content.textContent: Many organizations offer information and assistance to people living with cancer, but it's sometimes hard to know what resources can offer reliable and trustworthy support. Here is a list of excellent resources that can help you find information about cancer, treatment options, support groups in your community and financial and legal services. I encourage you to reach out to these organizations to learn how they can help you in your cancer journey.

content.name: Colorectal-Msg1
content.textContent: As we discussed, your next step is to complete the CTCA Authorization and Medical History forms. This process is easy to do online using the link below. If you do not have some of the information requested, simply save your work and return to it later. (For example, you should save your work if you need to stop to look up your doctors’ contact information.

content.name: LeadProspect-PhoneDoc Value-Msg1
content.textContent: So that I can schedule your evaluation quickly, please complete these forms as soon as possible and note that after seven days, the link above will expire. If you need assistance or have questions, please contact me directly at my phone number or email address below.
